benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: GET /1.0/kb/bundles/{bundleId}/tags - Retrieve bundle tags

covered: Valid Request scenarios with successful retrieval for various bundle/tag states (happy path TC01, TC02, TC03, TC04, TC05, TC17, TC18)
Empty response for bundle with no tags (TC06)
Extensive Query Parameters coverage (includedDeleted, audit FULL/MINIMAL, extra/unknown params) with multiple combinations
Authorization scenarios (401 unauthorized for missing/invalid tokens) (TC12, TC13)
Error handling and robustness (404 for non-existent bundle; 400 for invalid bundleId and invalid audit; API down scenarios 503/504) (TC07, TC08, TC09, TC11)
Performance and scalability considerations (large tag sets TC15; concurrency TC19; general performance expectations TC20)
Regression tests for deleted tags filtering (includedDeleted=false) and backward compatibility (no audit param) (TC17, TC18)
gaps: Pagination handling for large datasets is not tested
Caching behavior / caching headers (ETag, Cache-Control) are not tested
403 Forbidden authorization path is not explicitly tested (only 401 tested)
recommendations: Add dedicated pagination tests to validate paging behavior and limits
Add tests for caching headers to verify caching behavior (ETag, Cache-Control)
Add explicit 403 Forbidden tests for authorization scenarios
Add rate-limiting/throttle tests to validate burst traffic handling
Specify concrete performance targets/thresholds for different payload sizes and concurrency levels
Add tests for additional invalid query parameter formats to strengthen input validation
